<p>The <code>exists</code> function tests if a file exists in the APP directory.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}'index.pad' | exists{close}</pre>
<p>index.pad exists: <b>{'index.pad' | exists}</b></p>

<pre>{open}'nonexistent.pad' | exists{close}</pre>
<p>nonexistent.pad exists: <b>{'nonexistent.pad' | exists}</b></p>

<h2>Check Templates</h2>
<pre>{open}'fragments/claude/functions/index.pad' | exists{close}</pre>
<p>This file exists: <b>{'fragments/claude/functions/index.pad' | exists}</b></p>

<h2>Conditional Include</h2>
<pre>{open}if 'fragments/hello/hello.pad' | exists{close}
  File found
{open}else{close}
  File not found
{open}/if{close}</pre>
<p>Result: {if 'fragments/hello/hello.pad' | exists}File found{else}File not found{/if}</p>

<h2>Dynamic Path Check</h2>
<pre>{open}$path = 'index.pad'{close}
{open}if $path | exists{close}
  {open}$path{close} is available
{open}/if{close}</pre>
{data $path = 'index.pad'}
<p>Result: {if $path | exists}{$path} is available{/if}</p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>The path is relative to the APP directory. Use for checking optional templates or configuration files.</p>
